<hom role=""v""><pos>v</pos>
<sense n=""1""><number>1</number> <itype>[A3N2]</itype><trans> be in the early stages of pregnancy. </trans>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Ug musamkun (manamkun) ku, kasukaun ku,</i><trans> If I get pregnant, I feel like vomiting. </trans></eg>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Dílì makasamkun (makapanamkun) ang íyang asáwa kay dipiktúsu siyag matris,</i><trans> His wife cannot conceive because she has s.t. wrong with her uterus. </trans></eg>
</sense>
<sense n=""2""><number>2</number> <itype>[A13; c6]</itype><trans> <tr>conceive</tr> an idea in the mind. </trans>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Dílì mulibkas sa ngábil nang mga pulúnga ug wà pa na isamkun sa hunàhúnà,</i><trans> Those words would not have come out from the lips, if they had not been conceived in the mind. </trans></eg>
</sense></hom>
<entry><form id=""panamkun"" lang=""ceb""><abbr expan=""panamkun"" type=""lemma"">paN-</abbr></form>
<hom role=""v""><pos>v</pos>
<sense n=""1""><number>1</number> <itype>[A2]</itype><trans> develop a craving or dislike in early pregnancy. </trans>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Ang mabdus nanamkun ug manggang hilaw,</i><trans> The pregnant woman craved for green mangoes. </trans></eg>
</sense>
<sense n=""2""><number>2</number> <itype>[A23; c]</itype><trans> for a conceiving mother to have her child be like <pb n=""864""/>s.t. she has a liking or craving for. </trans>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Gipanamkun siyag iring maung kusug mulayat,</i><trans> When his mother was in her first few months with him, she took a liking to a cat. As a result he can jump high. </trans></eg>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Ayawg panamkúni ang bábuy,</i><trans> Don’t conceive a fondness for pigs or your baby will be like one. </trans></eg>
</sense></hom>
<hom role=""n""><pos>n</pos>
<sense n=""0""><trans> the cravings or dislikes one feels in early pregnancy.
</trans>
</sense></hom></entry></entry>");
